claim.claim-text:
10. An ionizing device for generating ionizing lines to shape solvent borne coating material being dispersed from an electrostatic rotary atomizer comprising: 
a band having a clamping element for affixing said device to the electrostatic rotary atomizer; 
a halo affixed to said band by at least one support arm; and said halo including a plurality of generally conical members spaced therearound generating ionic lines to shape the atomized coating material being dispersed from the rotary atomizer.

20. A method improving the transfer efficiency a coating materials dispersed in solvent and atomized by a rotary atomizer having an electric potential lower than ground potential comprising the steps of: 
affixing an ionizing device having conductive properties to said rotary atomizer; 
providing said ionizing device with a halo having a plurality of generally conical members dispersed therearound; 
generating ionic lines derived from the electrical potential from said rotary atomizer being transferred to said ionizing device; and 
shaping the spray pattern of the coating material with said ionic lines generated by said ionizing device.
